```julia
function clean_column(col::String)
    return lowercase(replace(col, r"[[:space:]]+" => "_"))
end
```

This function first lowers the case of the input string `col` and then replaces all sequences of whitespace characters with an underscore. The regular expression `r"[[:space:]]+"` matches one or more whitespace characters, including spaces, tabs, and line breaks.
